# Cursor Rules for Trail Safe

always:
  - Use JSDoc comments on all exported functions
  - Import from @/ not relative paths where possible
  - Use shadcn/ui components, never raw HTML inputs or buttons
  - Write tests alongside any new component or hook
  - Handle loading, error, and empty states in every data-fetching component
  - Use CSS token variables for colors, never hardcode hex values

never:
  - Call Firebase directly from a component
  - Use inline styles
  - Commit console.log statements
  - Skip error boundaries on pages

when writing hooks:
  - Return { data, loading, error } shape
  - Clean up Firestore listeners in useEffect return
  - Handle offline state gracefully

when writing Firestore helpers:
  - Always include try/catch
  - Log errors to console.error with context
  - Return null on failure, never throw to the caller
